# Day 3 - If-Else Statements

## Topics Learned

* Decision Making
* if-else Statements
* Conditional Logic

## What is if-else?

if-else is used to make decisions in a program.

## Syntax

```javascript
if (condition) {
    // code executes if condition is true
} else {
    // code executes if condition is false
}
```

## Example 1

```javascript
let age = 19;

if (age >= 18) {
    console.log("Adult");
} else {
    console.log("Minor");
}
```

Output:

```text
Adult
```

## Example 2

```javascript
let marks = 40;

if (marks >= 35) {
    console.log("Pass");
} else {
    console.log("Fail");
}
```

Output:

```text
Pass
```

## Common Comparison Operators

| Operator | Meaning                  |
| -------- | ------------------------ |
| >        | Greater Than             |
| <        | Less Than                |
| >=       | Greater Than or Equal To |
| <=       | Less Than or Equal To    |
| ===      | Strict Equal To          |
| !==      | Not Equal To             |

## Key Takeaways

* if executes when the condition is true.
* else executes when the condition is false.
* Conditions return either true or false.
* if-else helps programs make decisions.
